article.description: Deion Hammond and Ray Salnave each scored 12 points and Monmouth beat Iona 73-61 on Sunday.
article.headline: Hammond, Salnave send Monmouth past Iona 73-61
article.linkText: Hammond, Salnave send Monmouth past Iona 73-61
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. -- Deion Hammond and Ray Salnave each scored 12 points and Monmouth beat Iona 73-61 on Sunday. Monmouth (7-6, 1-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) led 33-28 at halftime before gradually creating safe space just before the midway point of the second half. Salnave made two foul shots and Melik Martin's layup with 12:30 left made it 46-34. Isaiah Ross made a 3-pointer two minutes later to reduce the Gaels' deficit to 49-41. George Papas followed with a jump shot and Monmouth led by double digits the rest of the way. The Hawks' bench outscored Iona 30-17. Iona's Ross -- who accounted for all the Gaels' (2-7, 0-2) bench points on 6-of-12 shooting with four 3s -- led the team in scoring. E.J. Crawford scored 15 and Tajaun Agee 12. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25
